<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900402-0056</DOCNO><DOCID>900402-0056.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Domtar Inc.:   Canadian, Some U.S. Assets   Of Salt Division Are Sold</HL><DATE>04/02/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   DTC</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><LP>   Domtar Inc. said it sold all Canadian and some U.S. assetsof its Sifto Salt division to North American Salt Co.,Mission, Kan. Terms weren't disclosed.   The sale largely completes the disposal of Domtar'schemical and energy interests, which the Montreal forest andbuilding-products concern began last year. A small specialtychemicals concern, Clough Chemicals Inc., remains to be sold.</LP><TEXT>   Domtar said the salt assets sold include a rock salt minein Goderich, Ontario, evaporated salt plants in Goderich,Amherst, Nova Scotia and Unity, Saskatchewan, Nickell SaltCo. in Saskatoon, Saskatchewan, and related distributionfacilities.</TEXT></DOC>